    {
      "number": 6,
      "id": "I_kwDORGnINM8AAAABFg96ZQ",
      "title": "Write section on timer algnment",
      "url": "https://github.com/teiclap/draft-porfiri-tsvwg-sctp-dtls-handshake/issues/6",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "gloinul",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Timer to remove old epoch needs to be longer than transmission timeout to ensure that all alloted time to deliver the TLS finished messages during rekying has been given. Otherwise the timer for removing the old keys will trigger prior to transmission failure timers. Which would deadlock the assocation anyway resulting association no-responsive timer triggering later. \n",
      "createdAt": "2026-06-15T12:31:16Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-15T16:01:22Z",
      "closedAt": "2026-06-15T16:01:22Z",
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 7,
      "id": "I_kwDORGnINM8AAAABFg-njg",
      "title": "Fix initial and restart sequence",
      "url": "https://github.com/teiclap/draft-porfiri-tsvwg-sctp-dtls-handshake/issues/7",
      "state": "CLOSED",
      "author": "gloinul",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "The initial and restart sequence can be aligned to install restart keys at the same time as protection required is set. \nRestart should clarify that protection required is set immendiatly (DTLS chunk?)\nSplit API calls into own sequence bullets compared to messages. ",
